subSubSection.paragraph:
Description.
Male genitalia (
Figs. 9­10
): Uncus short (0.39 X vavle length), thinner basally becoming broader toward apex. Valve elongate (length 8.1 X width), costal margin gently curved; ampulla elongate (0.10 X valve length); corona at apical 5% of valve length; sacculus well developed and 35% of valve length, distal margin not distinct and blends into valve. Aedoeagus slightly curved; vesica with 2 1/2 coils and minute spicules. Female genitalia (
Fig. 12
): Papillae anales triangulate, apex pointed. Eighth segment with fine spicules. Seventh segment with many large, robust setae in a row along distal margin; remainder of segment devoid of setae. Ductus bursae moderately elongate. Appendix bursae coiled. Corpus bursae ovate; signa composed of 4 scobinate bars.
